    <summary>AI-powered network design, config generation and automation platform</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
NetDesign AI is an open-source platform for AI-assisted network design and automation.

## Features
- Generate production-ready configs for Cisco IOS/NX-OS, Arista EOS, Juniper JunOS, and SONiC
- Design campus, DC, WAN, SD-WAN, and GPU fabric networks with AI guidance
- Simulate failure scenarios before touching live devices
- Deploy configs via Nornir/Netmiko with real-time progress
- Zero Touch Provisioning (ZTP)
- Native Claude AI integration via MCP server
- RBAC, audit trail, policy engine, and RCA analysis

## Requirements
- Docker Desktop must be installed and running
- 4 GB RAM minimum (8 GB recommended)
- Windows 10/11 64-bit
    ]]></description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/Amit33-design/Network-Automation/releases/tag/v2.4.0</releaseNotes>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency id="docker-desktop" version="4.0.0" />
    </dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="tools\**" target="tools" />
  </files>
